11. Advantages of R
Free and cross-platform


Extensive statistical capabilities


Rich ecosystem of packages


Excellent for research and education


Strong visualization support


12. Limitations of R
Slower with large datasets compared to Python


Memory usage is high (loads full dataset into RAM)


Steep learning curve for non-programmers


13. Applications of R
Academic Research â€“ statistical analysis


Healthcare â€“ disease modeling, bioinformatics


Finance â€“ risk analysis, portfolio optimization


Retail â€“ customer segmentation, sales forecasting


Machine Learning â€“ predictive modeling


 14. Conclusion
R is a powerful tool for data analysis and statistics. With its wide range of packages and capabilities, it is suitable for everything from academic projects to real-world machine learning applications. Learning R is a strong foundation for any aspiring data scientist.
